2. **"Will this look good on MY nails / fingers / skin tone?"** The single most repeated question across beauty community threads. Readers with shorter nail beds, wider fingers, or darker skin tones feel excluded by content that only shows one body type.
3. **"Is the classic white French tip outdated?"** High anxiety question — readers love the look but have heard conflicting signals. They want editorial confidence that the look is still current (and ideally, shown in its modern 2026 iterations).
4. **"How do I make it last without it looking obvious when it grows out?"** Practical longevity concern — especially relevant for gel and BIAB wearers. Smile line visibility on grow-out is a specific recurring complaint.
5. **"I can't afford the salon / I want to DIY this — what are my options?"** Press-on and at-home gel kit demand is surging. Readers want to know whether they need a professional to achieve the look or if a press-on set is a legitimate alternative.

